1. DataTypes
   1. Primitive Data Type [byte, short, int, long, float, double, char, boolean]
   a) To use them, we don't need to create objects
   b) The memory needed to store primitive data types is FIXED and we know this in advance

   2. Non-Primitive data Type [Class, Array, String....]
      a) To use them, we need to create objects
      b) The memory needed to store non-primitive data types is NOT FIXED and we don't know this in advance
